React Note App
This project is a simple, dynamic note-taking web application built with React.
Users can add, view, and delete notes in a clean, responsive interface inspired by Google Keep.

TABLE OF CONTENT

Overview
  - The challenge
  - Links

My process
  - Built with
  - What I learned

Author

OVERVIEW 

- The challenge

  Users should be able to:
    - Write and save short notes
    - Expand the note creation area on focus
    - Add a new note with a title and content
    - Delete individual notes
    - Interact with a smooth, minimal UI

- Links
    - GitHub: https://github.com/Argoneo
    - Deployed on netifly.app: notebookargone.netlify.app

- My process
  - Built with
    - React (Functional components + Hooks)
    - JavaScript (ES6)
    - HTML5
    - CSS3
    - Material-UI (Icons, Buttons, Animations)
    - Google Fonts (McLaren, Montserrat)
    - Responsive layout and clean design

- What I learned
  - How to use useState for local component state
  - How to lift state and manage child-to-parent communication
  - How to dynamically render components with .map()
  - How to handle simple form logic in React
  - How to integrate Material-UI for a polished interface
  - How to conditionally render UI based on state

